<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910114-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>910114-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- CompuAdd Corp.:   Computer Contract Awarded   For Operation Desert Shield</HL><DATE>01/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   CompuAdd Corp., Austin, Texas, said it was awarded a $21million contract to supply the U.S. military with more than1,700 desktop and laptop computers for Operation DesertShield. The company expects to deliver the last of thecomputers to Saudi Arabia today.   The contract, which was awarded last year, requiredCompuAdd to deliver the computers before tomorrow, a CompuAddspokesman said. The PCs are used for behind-the-linesadministration on land and at sea.</LP><TEXT>   The Department of Defense selected CompuAdd machines andpaid for them through the Gulf Peace Fund, which was createdto administer a $2 billion contribution pledged by Japan forthe operation, CompuAdd said. Closely held CompuAdd hasannual sales of more than $400 million.</TEXT></DOC>